Pre-Game Insights: Not many gave Australia much hope in this T20 World Cup after heavy series defeats in Bangladesh and the Caribbean.
However, Australia bucked expectations by finishing second in Group 1, recording four wins and just one defeat.
Pakistan have ridden a wave of euphoria all the way to the semis, winning all their matches so far.
Spinners are going to be very important in this match â€” in six of the 11 games to take place in Dubai, a spinner has taken man of the match honours, including Adam Zampa. Twice.
The average first innings score at Dubai in this tournament is 122, but that average is skewed horribly by some woeful efforts by West Indies, Bangladesh and Scotland.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia has played three games at Dubai for wins over Sri Lanka and Bangladesh (when batting second) and a defeat to England (when batting first).
Pakistan, meanwhile, have won more games in Dubai in T20 cricket than any other team has even played. From 27 games, Pakistan has won 16 in Dubai, with 10 losses and one tie.
Australia has played 23 T20 Internationals against Pakistan, winning nine.
